(1007, 'WL', 'A', '127', 'L', 'S', NULL, 'Mime type', NULL, 'A media type (also known as a Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions or MIME type) indicates the nature and format of a document, file, or assortment of bytes. MIME types are defined and standardized in IETF\'s RFC 6838.', 'Extension: pdf.\r\nMime types. \'application/pdf\', \'application/acrobat\', \'application/nappdf\', \'application/x-pdf\', \'image/pdf\'.', 'If unknown, use the file extension, the system will guess the best mime type.', 'When the url force a file to download or open in the browser using HTML.', '2022-11-27 23:52:23', '2022-11-28 00:10:29'),
